By Sylvester Idowu in Warri, Omon-Julius Onabu in Asaba and Adibe Emenyonu in Benin City The remains of the former Military Administrator of the defunct Mid-Western region (now Edo and Delta states), Maj. Gen. David Ejoor (Rtd.) were laid to rest yesterday in his hometown, Ovwor, Olomu Kingdom in Ughelli South Local Government area of Delta State, with dignitaries, including a former Head of State, General Yakubu Gowon, describing him as a true patriot.